HEADWORD: Munjistin
<hw>Mun"jis*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An orange-red coloring substance resembling alizarin, found in the
root of an East Indian species of madder (<spn>Rubia
munjista</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Munnion</ent>⟦br⟧
